commitResults.messageBody: Implemented a skeletal version of Duke that starts by greeting the user, simply echos commands entered by the user, and exits when the user types bye
Added the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested.
- Created Task.java and added necessary fields and its getters
- Added the ability to mark tasks as done. Optionally, add the ability to change the status back to not done.

commitResults.messageTitle: Added and Implements Deadline, Event and Todo classes
commitResults.messageBody: Added and Implemented Deadline, Event and Todo classes that inherits from Task class

Completed Level 4 by implementing the necessary logic in Duke.java file.
- Added: Events, Todo and Deadline tasks

Completed A-TextUiTesting
-Used the input/output redirection technique to semi-automate the testing of Duke.

commitResults.messageTitle: Created and Implemented Duke and Todo exception classes
commitResults.messageBody: Created and Implemented Duke and Todo exception classes

The program now handles the following errors
- Unknown commands
- missing description for tasks (todo, event, deadline)
- missing index for mark/unmark
- blank user input

Added support for deleting tasks from the list.
The program now handles the following errors
- missing index for deletion of task
- index out of range for deletion of task
Used enums to represent command keywords from user input
Save the tasks in the hard disk automatically whenever the task list changes. Load the data from the hard disk when Duke starts up. Data file location is [project_root]/data/duke.txt
For Deadline and Event tasks, date data provided is now saved as LocalDateTime data. Duke now accepts date time input in dd-MM-yyyy HHmm and output the date data in MMM dd yyyy format.
